name: Inverse Human Disturbance
notes: Inverse with low values describing high disturbance and vice versa, use for zonation

name: Classified Human Disturbance
notes: Reclassified to Low Medium High disturbance

name: el
notes: eelgrass: intertidal & shallow subtidal eelgrass beds.

name: bs
notes: beaches: well- to sparsely-vegetated or non-vegetated beaches and shorelines.

name: mf
notes: mudflats: non-vegetated mudflats or with varying amounts of algae.

name: vs
notes: vegetated shoreline: low-lying rocky shoreline, soil pockets in rock cracks and crevices; salt-tolerant vegetation, generally with < 20% vegetation cover.

name: cs
notes: coastal herbaceous: criteria as for ‘hb’ but influenced by proximity to ocean; windswept shoreline and slopes; > 20% vegetation of grasses, herbs, mosses and lichens.

name: Streams
notes: Raster value 3 for fish-bearing streams, 2 for non-fish bearing, 1 for drainage channel and NA
